    <type>Lander</type>
    <naif_host_id>-244</naif_host_id>
    <description>Peregrine is a small lander designed for delivering payloads to lunar orbit and the lunar surface. It features a versatile payload mounting system, side radiators, a top-mounted solar panel, and is constructed from aluminum alloy with four shock-absorbing landing legs. The thermal environment is regulated passively through radiators and protective layers like Multi-Layer Insulation (MLI). Peregrine's propulsion system includes five main engines and twelve Attitude and Control System (ACS) engines that utilize a hypergolic bipropellant, allowing for ignition-free combustion. The Guidance, Navigation, and Control (GNC) system incorporates various sensors, and a Doppler LiDAR assists in landing. The power system operates with a lithium-ion battery and solar panel, distributing power to all subsystems. Communication is facilitated via a high-powered transponder with multiple antennas for efficient coverage during different mission phases.</description>
